@EndifDoc
@EndDescription
@EndOperator


@BeginParameter noffset
@Item = nsets
INTEGER  Number of input time steps for each output time step
@Item = noffset
INTEGER  Number of input time steps skipped before the first time step range (optional)
@Item = nskip
INTEGER  Number of input time steps skipped between time step ranges (optional)
@EndParameter


@BeginExample
Assume an input dataset has monthly means over several years.
To compute seasonal means from monthly means the first two
month must be skipped:
@BeginVerbatim
   cdo selmean,3,2 ifile ofile
@EndVerbatim
@EndExample
